<p>a long time, I dont know where we are going to hold it, She is nice &amp; sunny &amp; the ground is drying fast.<br/>Our rations are a little short lately &amp; the Sergts (all hungry dogs) are generally a day in front of their issue &amp; worst of all we cant buy any bread for love nor money. Yesterday was pay day again <br/>Had old Mac for our parson on this morning's church parade &amp; he preached quite a good sermon  General Walker &amp; Leslie were also there, they were to have made an inspection of our huts but they have not done so as yet.<br/>12th Was busy writing letters last night when someone said there is an officer wants to see you. I looked</p>
